# Overview

This section gives a structured overview of embodied intelligence as a research area.

## Scope

Embodied intelligence sits at the intersection of:

- perception
- action
- control
- planning
- language
- world modeling
- physical interaction

## Core Questions

- How should an embodied agent represent the world?
- How should it connect perception to action?
- How can it generalize across tasks, objects, and embodiments?
- How should physical constraints be incorporated?
- How can simulation knowledge transfer to the real world?

## Main Subfields

- Vision-Language-Action
- World Models
- Manipulation
- Grasping
- Affordance Learning
- Navigation
- 3D Perception
- Sim2Real
- Benchmarking and Evaluation

More detailed topic pages will be added progressively.
